    {
        "url": "/quotes/tess_gerritsen_608277",
        "quote": "Writing is very much an emotional process; it requires you to be very in touch with your feelings. That is the opposite of what you're taught as a medical doctor. We're supposed to be detached and logical. Maybe because I started off as a writer and then became a doctor, I'm able to integrate those two.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Tess Gerritsen",
            "url": "/quotes/tess_gerritsen_608277"
        },
        "topics": [
